caption: Rights and Responsibilities of Parents/Guardians
created: 20260405120000000
modified: 20260405120000000
title: Policy6005(s2)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Nonetheless, the Board acknowledges the right of parents/guardians to instruct their children at home as an alternative to public school attendance. The Board recognizes state law and Connecticut State Board of Education policy and guidance relating to home instruction. Accordingly, the Board permits home instruction of a child who would otherwise be attending public school if the person having control of such school-aged child is able to show that the child is receiving equivalent instruction in the studies taught in the public schools elsewhere.

Parents/guardians intending to provide home instruction for their children are required to contact the Superintendent to make the appropriate arrangements. Failure to do so may result in a non-enrolled child being considered truant from school.
